==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hard-tack
<hw>Hard"-tack`</hw></mhw>
<pr>(h⟦aum⟧rd"t⟦acr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A name
given by soldiers and sailors to a kind of unleavened hard biscuit or
sea bread. Called also <altname>pilot biscuit</altname>, <altname>pilot
bread</altname>, <altname>ship biscuit</altname> and <altname>ship
bread</altname></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any of several mahogany trees, esp. the
<spn>Cercocarpus betuloides</spn>.</def> <au>MW10</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hardtail</ent>⟦br⟧
